WorkItem.Description:
I'm creating typescript definitions for SharePoint 2013. Some classes have members witch can be string or function. In this case I have to use any type and not rely on type checking.

Sum types (OR-types) can solve this problem. I can specify 
```
interface ISomething {
    Body: string | (ctx) => string;
}
```
And compiler will check assigngments and implicitly coerce type to one of types in sum.

Thank you.
